# HTML Standards

## Base Template

Every HTML page should follow this structure:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta name="description" content="Page description here">
    <title>Page Title | My Retro Blog</title>
    
    <!-- Tailwind CSS -->
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
    <script>
        tailwind.config = {
            theme: {
                extend: {
                    fontFamily: {
                        'comic': ['"Comic Sans MS"', 'cursive'],
                        'times': ['"Times New Roman"', 'serif'],
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>
    <!-- Content here -->
    
    <!-- jQuery at bottom -->
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>
    <script src="./assets/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

## Content vs Presentation

**HTML = Structure ONLY. Content = JSON files.**

- HTML elements use IDs for JavaScript targeting: `<h1 id="site-title"></h1>`
- All dynamic text content loaded from `data/*.json` files
- Use HTML comments as reminders: `<!-- Content loaded from content.json -->`

## Accessibility Basics

- Always include `alt` text for images: `<img src="fire.gif" alt="Decorative flames">`
- Use semantic elements: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`
- Ensure sufficient color contrast for text readability

## Script Placement

- Tailwind CDN in `<head>` (needs to load first for styles)
- jQuery and custom scripts at bottom of `<body>`
